Full Description: Sometimes, things are meant to  happen.   Call it fate…call it the order of the  universe.  But when Jon Hirsch, CEO of ALL-STAR SPORTS MANAGEMENT, met Dirk Saecker, an experienced real estate professional with an incredible network of national and international clients, there was no doubt that ALL-STAR REALTY & INVESTMENTS, LLC, would come to be. This friendship and partnership has led to an incredibly dynamic and fast-growing organization that combines the world of sports and entertainment with the world of national and international  real estate.     Today, they’re changing the game for realtors,  home buyers and sellers and  investors by offering a ‘one-stop shop’ for all their needs.  Whether it’s temporary housing for a celebrity, or an industrial complex for an investor or a luxury condo, the world of  ALL-STAR is offering everything from brokers,mortgage services, short sales and  REOs, to title services  and public relations or marketing. Jon and Dirk have built a team of professionals that understands their over-riding credo:  Provide outstanding client service                                                                                                  _________________________________________________________________________                                                                              ALL-STAR  REALTY  & INVESTMENTS , LLC All-Star Realty & Investments is the real estate division of All-Star Sports Management, a leading full -service management company,  offering a full range of services to home buyers and sellers. DIRK  SAECKER, BROKER Dirk was a recognized tourism and hospitality leader in his  homeland of Germany, and when he moved to the United States in 1990, he continued his tourism and hospitality career.  With a large network of international professionals as his clients, it was a natural transition to move into the real estate field, specializing in commercial properties and investments, and he soon became Commercial Director of a major real estate firm in Miami, where he was consistently among the top five producers.  In 2013, he partnered with Jon Hirsch, who was CEO of All-Star  Sports Management, to create the real estate division, All-Star Realty & Investments, LLC.  Dirk brings over a decade of  expertise to All-Star Realty & Investments, using his entrepreneurial skills and business acumen to handle all types of  real estate, ranging from complex commercial transactions to luxury residential sales rentals, short sales and  REOs.

They do anything from a basic clean out to a complete makeover in multi-million dollar homes.   They have a very unique approach to the projects, combining the services needed to do the makeover with the products.  They are not a franchise that has to order from a specific catalog of products.  They order everything CUSTOM.  Because they are in higher end homes dealing with customers with a good deal of disposable income, but are very time poor, they combing a wide array of products they have access to, design an upgraded space, along with a list of services to get the job done with just one company.  They supply a temporary storage container to store belingings in while they are working on the garage, a professional organizer helps with the sorting  their items to see what will be kept, trashed, donated, etc., then they do any repair and painting necessary,  electrical and plumbing is done when needed, floors are installed, new cabinets and shelving are installed, and then they have organizer come back to clean everything and put it all away in bins and tubs, right down to the labeling of their belongings.  This combination of products and services has given us a HUGE advantage in their market, and let us compete with some major franchises who do not offer any of these services and are stuck ordering from what their catalog of products carries.  They have had a huge success rate and are in a position with their vendors to start bulk buying and saving huge amounts on shipping.  They have had to hire additional people and need to add additional vehicles to the operations to keep up with what has booked.  They are looking to expand here and take this idea to other cities.

As search engine results grow larger, the frustration of traditional search is the time spent sifting through those results. What if someone credible had already packaged up the links/content you needed and made them available for purchase at a reasonable price?  SearchMyResearch.com enables users to aggregate and package links and/or proprietary content - their "research" - dealing with a particular subject, market it, and track interest via their "Sales Management Center" on our site. It is free to become a Seller. Buyers will come seeking specific content via marketing efforts of the Seller and through traditional search engines. Those searching for specific content will be taken to the Seller's "Pitch page" (think: back cover of a traditional book) where the Seller makes his/her case to the Buyer and establishes their credibility. A Buyer need only then hit the "purchase" button to purchase that "research." The page of links can then be saved to the Buyer's favorites and accessed at their leisure. If the research Buyers are looking for doesn't yet exist on our site, they can opt-in to be notified when it is. To encourage transactions, Sellers who may have already done the needed research will be able to mark demand and offer their research for sale.  We recognize that people are looking for credible guides and we believe they are willing to pay for that guidance. Rather than hire those guides, we incentivize the global market and hope they will bubble up at the prospect of being able to "profit from their experience." Description: Zeelfa provides users with referrals for a wide variety of services and products.
Headquarters Regions: Dallas/Fort Worth Metroplex, Southern US
Full Description: Zeelfa is an innovative social networking site that allows members to refer their friends and family to their own trusted service professionals. From dentists to lawn care to medical services, Zeelfa exists to help users refer and find the highest quality professionals based on recommendations of their own friends and family. Finding a trustworthy service provider can be a daunting process. Zeelfa, a referral site for services, gives members the ability to recommend professional service providers to their friends and family. At heart, the concept is very different from other seemingly similar sites. Other sites focus on their members leaving a review for service providers they have used. Zeelfa is based on a different concept – the focus here is on recommending a provider to friends and family who need those services, and incorporating major social networking tools.  Zeelfa is all about answering pertinent questions and addressing problems, some of which include: 1.	Finding Trustworthy Service Providers: Trust is an important concern for customers looking to hire a new service 2.	Most review sites are biased 3.	Most classified sites are anonymous 4.	There are no easy ways to know of your friend’s and family member’s service providers Like members of social networking sites, Zeelfa members can create a full profile, complete with a profile picture, demographic information and more. They can invite friends and family to sign up as well, and they can begin searching for service providers used by their connections. For example, they can find out who their Uncle Robert uses for his automotive service or who their friend Janet goes to for dental work. As such, Zeelfa includes a wide range of categories and subcategories, and is continuously adding more.  Finding referrals is as simple as clicking the “Referrals” tab on the top menu and choosing the “Find Referrals” option from the dropdown menu that appears. On the next page, users are presented with the ability to search for the category of service they need, the keywords they wish to use and their location. Referring a service is just as simple. A user simply clicks on “Refer a Service” and then does a quick check to make sure the service is not yet listed. Then, they simply input the information required and the listing is complete.  To find out more about this innovative network and begin referring services, visit http://www.Zeelfa.com.

Description: Independent energy company.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: They have been involved in the energy industry since 1968. they began to expand their operations at the end of fiscal 1998 when they acquired The Atlas Group, Inc., an energy finance and production company located in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania. Since fiscal 1998, they have achieved consistent growth in their reserve base through developmental drilling activities, acquisitions of properties and, in 1999, the acquisition of Viking Resources Corporation, a North Canton, Ohio exploration and production company. From October 1, 1998 through September 30, 2003, proved reserves net to their interest grew from 93.3 Bcfe to 144.4 Bcfe, and the PV-10 value of these reserves grew from $49.2 million to $191.4 million. During the same period, proved reserves they manage for their drilling investment partnerships grew from 142.0 Bcfe to 187.8 Bcfe, and the PV-10 value of these reserves grew from $97.6 million to $273.5 million. As of September 30, 2003, they had an acreage position of approximately 431,000 gross (379,000 net) acres, of which 205,000 gross (190,000 net) acres were undeveloped. They have also achieved substantial growth in their drilling activities. The number of net wells they have drilled increased from 145 wells in fiscal 1999 to 282 wells in fiscal 2003. They expect that they will drill approximately 530 wells in fiscal 2004. Of the 1,111 wells they drilled in the past five fiscal years, they have completed approximately 99% as producing.
